CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, pg. 2, reads: "Loves Parades - Carl Redwood Jr., 3, of 836 Shawnee Street, 'cools it' with ice cream while indulging in another of this favorite pastimes - watching a parade. He is the sone of Mr. and Mrs. Carl Redwood Sr. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Carl Redwood Jr. wearing patterned bow tie and light colored cap, holding ice cream cup, and seated at bottom of steps of stone building while watching parade
